---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="AI Video Studio" description="AutoVideo turns a single prompt into a complete video package with script, scenes, voice, and music.">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-grid">
      <div>
        <span class="badge">No login • Mocked generation</span>
        <h1>Turn one prompt into a finished video story.</h1>
        <p>
          AutoVideo is a creative AI studio that drafts your script, storyboard, voice, and motion in minutes.
          Share mock previews instantly and refine before production.
        </p>
        <div class="taglist" style="margin: 1.5rem 0;">
          <span class="tag">English-first</span>
          <span class="tag">Multiple demos</span>
          <span class="tag">Cloudflare ready</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a class="button primary" href="/create">Start a mock build</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/demos">See demo gallery</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-card">
        <h3>Live mock session</h3>
        <p>Prompt: “Launch a futuristic smart bike in Tokyo.”</p>
        <div class="steps" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
          <div class="step"><span>Script & hook</span><strong>done</strong></div>
          <div class="step"><span>Scene layout</span><strong>done</strong></div>
          <div class="step"><span>Voice & music</span><strong>processing</strong></div>
          <div class="step"><span>Export preview</span><strong>queued</strong></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title">
        <span>Why AutoVideo</span>
        <h2>Everything you need to mock a full video in one place.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Prompt-to-Storyboard</h3>
          <p>Generate structured scenes with shots, pacing, and transitions from a single sentence.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>AI Voice & Music</h3>
          <p>Hear a draft voiceover and soundtrack instantly to validate tone before production.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Instant Previews</h3>
          <p>Share mock previews for stakeholder approval without touching a timeline editor.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>No Login Required</h3>
          <p>Start exploring immediately. Every flow here is a safe, non-production mock.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title">
        <span>Mock Creation Flow</span>
        <h2>Preview every step before you render the final video.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>1. Prompt intake</h3>
          <p>Describe the goal, style, audience, and duration. AutoVideo structures it automatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>2. AI script pass</h3>
          <p>Receive a full script with hooks, pacing, and a clear CTA.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>3. Scene rehearsal</h3>
          <p>Get a visual storyboard and camera directions for every scene.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>4. Mock playback</h3>
          <p>Play a low-latency preview with temporary audio and subtitles.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title">
        <span>Customer sentiment</span>
        <h2>Teams love the fast mock feedback loop.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="quote">“We validated our product launch video in 15 minutes. The mock felt real enough to brief production.”</div>
          <strong>— Talia P., Growth Lead</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="quote">“AutoVideo helped us align five stakeholders on tone before filming a single frame.”</div>
          <strong>— Mark R., Creative Director</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="quote">“The demo prompts are priceless. We finally show clients something tangible in the first call.”</div>
          <strong>— Amina L., Studio Owner</strong>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
